# Release distributable and installer

Part of the end-of-task workflow in `task-completion.mdc` — run this **before** committing, after
any Desktop-affecting change. Do not leave only a Debug build.

Run from the repo root:

```powershell
powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File "installer/build-release.ps1"
```

Use `"C:\Program Files\dotnet\dotnet.exe"` if `dotnet` in PATH resolves to the wrong SDK (x86 stub without SDK 8).

Expected outputs (gitignored under `release/`):

- `release/publish/` — self-contained win-x64 Release publish
- `release/EvEMapEnhanced-Setup-<version>.exe` — Inno Setup installer (when ISCC is installed)

If Inno Setup is missing, the script falls back to a zip in `release/`; note that in the task summary and keep the `.iss` script ready for the next run.

Do not stage `release/`, `bin/`, or `obj/` in git commits.
